CRITICAL — Do not over-penalize hedging language: Articles written by exchanges, blogs, or analysts that use cautious framing ("no prediction is guaranteed," "investors should remain vigilant," "cautiously optimistic") while presenting exclusively bullish analytical content should NOT be scored lower than 14. The forward-looking analytical substance determines the score, not the disclaimer language.

